  "commentary": "With SPX at 7025.62 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and max positive gamma at 7050, dealers are currently in a neutral hedging zone but approaching the heavy selling wall. The PIN regime with massive positive GEX walls clustered tightly between 7000-7050 creates a strong magnet effect, where dealers will aggressively sell any push toward 7050 and provide buying support on dips back toward 7000-7015. Key levels to watch are the 7015 negative gamma pocket for potential bounce support and the 7050 wall where dealer selling should cap upside momentum.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pinned between 7015-7050 with limited breakout potential.",
